- "stormy captains" metaphorically refers to the users (captains) who experienced severe issues (storms) with their devices; 
- "ships" refer to the devices (device_id); 
- "unquelled tempests" represent unresolved high-severity events (resolved = 0 and severity = 'high');
- "windy month of April" refers to the period from April 1, 2023, to April 30, 2023.

- "beacons" refers to monitoring devices;
- "currents of active service" or "currently docked for repairs" refers to the status of 'active' or 'maintenance';
- "journey maps" refers to the location;
- "flags they fly" refers to the device_type;
- "compass guiding their navigation" refers to the firmware_version;
- "recalibration within the last lunar cycle" means the event_type is 'calibration' and the event_time is within the last 30 days.

- "whispering to the universe" metaphorically refers to devices signaling low severity events;
- "low-risk dance" means engaging in activities categorized as low severity;
- The context of "this month" suggests the timeframe within which the events are counted;
- A count greater than two is considered "more than twice".

- 'gadgets' refers to monitoring devices;
- 'central site' corresponds to 'Site A';
- 'the last month' refers to May 2023.
